- It's not what I believe in.

495
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:25,067
That joke you pulled with Hilly
with the toilets, that's funny.

496
00:42:26,571 --> 00:42:28,562
Why would you do this to us?

497
00:42:29,541 --> 00:42:31,133
I don't even know why you care.

498
00:42:31,309 --> 00:42:34,142
- What?
- Things are fine around here.

499
00:42:34,312 --> 00:42:35,745
Why go stir up trouble?

500
00:42:35,881 --> 00:42:38,281
Trouble's already here, Stuart.

501
00:42:38,417 --> 00:42:40,408
I had to tell you this.
You needed to know.

502
00:42:40,552 --> 00:42:43,453
Goddamn right I needed to know. You
should have told me this from the start.

503
00:42:48,226 --> 00:42:49,887
You're a selfish woman, Skeeter.

504
00:42:51,730 --> 00:42:52,788
Stuart.

505
00:42:52,931 --> 00:42:55,092
I think you're better off being alone.

506
00:43:43,248 --> 00:43:44,806
Yeah.

507
00:43:44,950 --> 00:43:47,748
Did you get to that part yet
that I was telling you about?

508
00:43:47,853 --> 00:43:49,787
Don't read ahead, whatever you do.

509
00:43:49,921 --> 00:43:52,219
"What you done put up in this?"

510
00:43:52,390 --> 00:43:55,791
"She said, 'My shit."'

511
00:44:10,642 --> 00:44:12,200
What's the matter, Hilly?

512
00:44:13,678 --> 00:44:17,478
- Get off of me! Get off!
- Ouch! Stop hitting me!

513
00:44:19,551 --> 00:44:22,213
I heard that Betty character
might be Mary Elizabeth.

514
00:44:22,354 --> 00:44:24,788
It's not Jackson.

515
00:44:24,890 --> 00:44:29,327
And that book is garbage. I bet the
whole thing is made up by some nigra.

516
00:44:29,461 --> 00:44:31,395
And Jolene, didn't your mama

517
00:44:31,530 --> 00:44:33,555
leave Cora to you in her will?

518
00:44:33,698 --> 00:44:37,657
Yes, but that's not odd, is it?
Happens all the time, right?

519
00:44:37,802 --> 00:44:40,532
The book is not about Jackson.

520
00:46:05,423 --> 00:46:06,947
What the hell?

521
00:46:08,260 --> 00:46:09,784
What are you doing here?

522
00:46:11,630 --> 00:46:13,928
I've contacted my lawyer.

523
00:46:14,065 --> 00:46:16,693
Hibbie Goodman? He's the best
libel attorney in the state.

524
00:46:16,868 --> 00:46:18,495
Oh, Missy, you're going to jail.

525
00:46:18,637 --> 00:46:20,434
You can't prove anything.

526
00:46:20,572 --> 00:46:23,939
Oh, I 100 percent know you wrote it.
Nobody else in town is as tacky as you.

527
00:46:24,075 --> 00:46:25,975
You don't know anything, Hilly.

528
00:46:26,111 --> 00:46:27,635
Oh, I don't, do I?

529
00:46:28,280 --> 00:46:31,340
You tell Aibileen the next time
she wants to write

530
00:46:31,483 --> 00:46:34,384
about my dear friend Elizabeth...

531
00:46:34,552 --> 00:46:38,488
Uh-huh.
Remember her? Had you in her wedding.

532
00:46:38,623 --> 00:46:41,854
Let's just say Aibileen ought to have
been a little bit smarter

533
00:46:41,993 --> 00:46:44,689
before putting in about that
L-shaped scratch

534
00:46:44,829 --> 00:46:47,525
in poor Elizabeth's dining table.

535
00:46:49,601 --> 00:46:53,401
And that nigger Minny,
do I have plans for her.

536
00:46:54,039 --> 00:46:58,874
Careful, Hilly. That's chapter 12.

537
00:46:59,010 --> 00:47:01,205
Don't give yourself away now.

538
00:47:01,646 --> 00:47:03,307
That was not me!

539
00:47:04,182 --> 00:47:06,377
I've come to tell your mother
what a hippie you've become.

540
00:47:06,518 --> 00:47:08,611
She's going to be disgusted by you.

541
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:12,383
Why, Hilly. Is everything OK, you two?

542
00:47:12,524 --> 00:47:13,548
Oh, Mrs Phelan.

543
00:47:13,692 --> 00:47:17,628
Hilly, you're a sweaty mess.
Are you ill?

544
00:47:18,463 --> 00:47:19,487
No, ma'am.

545
00:47:19,631 --> 00:47:24,625
Darling, oh, no husband wants
to come home and see that.

546
00:47:24,936 --> 00:47:26,563
Oh.

547
00:47:26,705 --> 00:47:28,195
I didn't have time to get fixed up.

548
00:47:28,340 --> 00:47:30,331
You know, Hilly, if I didn't
know any better,

549
00:47:30,475 --> 00:47:34,172
I'd say you've been eating too much pie.

550
00:47:38,616 --> 00:47:41,915
Mrs Phelan, I came here...

551
00:47:42,053 --> 00:47:44,578
In fact, I'm sure of it.

552
00:47:44,723 --> 00:47:46,987
Now you get your raggedy ass
off my porch.

553
00:47:47,625 --> 00:47:49,525
Go on.

554
00:47:49,661 --> 00:47:52,755
Get off my property. Now!

555
00:47:53,832 --> 00:47:57,097
Before we all get one of those
disgusting things on our lips!

556
00:48:12,417 --> 00:48:15,716
Eugenia. Take me inside, please.

557
00:48:16,788 --> 00:48:17,812
Yes, ma'am.

558
00:48:33,438 --> 00:48:36,532
Skeeter, do you have plans tomorrow?

559
00:48:37,142 --> 00:48:38,803
- No, ma'am.
- Good.

560
00:48:40,478 --> 00:48:43,038
Because we are going shopping.

561
00:48:44,916 --> 00:48:47,407
No single daughter of mine is
going to New York City

562
00:48:47,552 --> 00:48:49,144
representing the great state
of Mississippi

563
00:48:49,287 --> 00:48:51,755
without a proper cosmopolitan wardrobe.

564
00:48:51,890 --> 00:48:53,289
How do you know about New York?

565
00:48:53,425 --> 00:48:56,258
Oh, well, Miss Stein called last night.

566
00:49:03,935 --> 00:49:06,870
Courage sometimes skips a generation.

567
00:49:09,808 --> 00:49:12,641
Thank you for bringing it back
to our family.

568
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:24,081
I can't leave you like this.

569
00:49:24,522 --> 00:49:27,685
Eugenia, I have made a decision.

570
00:49:27,826 --> 00:49:30,317
My health's been on the uptick
these last few weeks,

571
00:49:30,462 --> 00:49:33,659
and I know the doctor says it's
some kind of last strength nonsense,

572
00:49:33,798 --> 00:49:38,235
but I have decided not to die.

573
00:49:43,741 --> 00:49:44,901
Oh, Mama.

574
00:49:45,076 --> 00:49:46,805
It's too late.
I tried calling Fanny Mae's

575
00:49:46,945 --> 00:49:49,209
to make all your hair appointments
for the next 20 years,

576
00:49:49,347 --> 00:49:51,815
but they wouldn't allow it.

577
00:49:54,085 --> 00:49:58,545
I have never been more proud of you.

578
00:50:03,461 --> 00:50:05,190
Thank you.

579
00:50:13,805 --> 00:50:15,204
Mama.

580
00:50:43,368 --> 00:50:44,892
Need some help with those?

581
00:50:47,038 --> 00:50:48,266
Minny.

582
00:50:48,406 --> 00:50:50,306
- Miss Celia!
- Minny, hey, stop! Minny!

583
00:50:50,475 --> 00:50:52,102
- Miss Celia!
- Minny!

584
00:50:52,243 --> 00:50:56,179
- Stay back!
- I'm not here to hurt you! Girl...

585
00:50:58,049 --> 00:50:59,744
You gonna put the stick down?

586
00:50:59,884 --> 00:51:01,613
Uh-uh.

587
00:51:04,255 --> 00:51:07,850
Listen, Celia finally told me
about the babies.

588
00:51:09,027 --> 00:51:10,392
All of them.

589
00:51:12,163 --> 00:51:15,860
But I also know, the minute
you started working here,

590
00:51:15,967 --> 00:51:17,867
she started getting better.

591
00:51:18,937 --> 00:51:20,802
So, you saved her life.

592
00:51:24,242 --> 00:51:26,972
You knew I was here the whole time?

593
00:51:27,111 --> 00:51:30,444
Fried chicken and okra
on the first night?

594
00:51:31,616 --> 00:51:34,141
Y'all could have at least put
some cornpone on the table.

595
00:51:36,921 --> 00:51:38,013
No.

596
00:51:39,657 --> 00:51:42,023
I couldn't let you eat no more cornpone,
Mr Johnny.

597
00:51:42,193 --> 00:51:45,026
Thanks to you, now I've had to let out
every pair of pants I own.

598
00:51:53,004 --> 00:51:55,370
You just leave that.

599
00:51:56,007 --> 00:51:57,372
Here you go.

600
00:51:58,343 --> 00:52:00,038
Let's head on up the house.

601
00:52:24,702 --> 00:52:25,828
What's this?

602
00:52:26,671 --> 00:52:28,366
I cooked it all by myself.

603
00:52:28,506 --> 00:52:31,134
Yes, she did.
She was up all night.

604
00:52:32,710 --> 00:52:34,837
I wanted to do something special.

605
00:52:36,114 --> 00:52:38,207
I wanted to say thank you.

606
00:52:41,352 --> 00:52:42,376
So...

607
00:52:43,388 --> 00:52:45,015
...I ain't losing my job?

608
00:52:46,991 --> 00:52:50,688
No, you got a job here
for the rest of your life.

609
00:52:50,828 --> 00:52:52,056
If you want it.

610
00:52:58,403 --> 00:53:00,530
That's a mile-high meringue, Miss Celia.

611
00:53:09,981 --> 00:53:12,245
- Please.
- Thank you.

612
00:53:16,220 --> 00:53:18,188
Ooh.

613
00:53:18,322 --> 00:53:19,789
You remember to check the thighs?

614
00:53:19,957 --> 00:53:23,552
- Mm-hm. Cooked clean through.
- Ain't pink in the middle?

615
00:53:23,695 --> 00:53:26,892
Uh-uh. Just the way you taught me.

616
00:53:27,031 --> 00:53:28,931
Looky here.

617
00:53:32,737 --> 00:53:35,763
<i>That table of food</i>
<i>gave Minny the strength she needed.</i>

618
00:53:36,908 --> 00:53:41,436
<i>She took her babies out from under Leroy</i>
<i>and never went back.</i>

619
00:53:45,983 --> 00:53:48,611
What are all these cars
doing out here? Are we late?

620
00:53:48,753 --> 00:53:50,118
No, we ain't late.

621
00:53:51,723 --> 00:53:52,781
Why ain't you singing?

622
00:53:52,924 --> 00:53:55,085
We got to worry about getting
in there and getting our seats.

623
00:53:55,226 --> 00:53:56,454
Come on now, we late!

624
00:54:05,403 --> 00:54:08,736
- Who we clapping for?
- Honey, we clapping for you!

625
00:54:12,243 --> 00:54:13,972
Come on down, Sister Clark!

626
00:54:14,879 --> 00:54:16,073
Come on.

627
00:54:34,232 --> 00:54:35,665
Come on.

628
00:54:38,436 --> 00:54:39,801
All right, all right.

629
00:54:41,405 --> 00:54:46,604
Now, uh... this is an important time
in our community.

630
00:54:47,378 --> 00:54:51,644
And we have to thank you
for what you have done.

631
00:54:53,985 --> 00:54:55,145
Now...

632
00:54:56,254 --> 00:54:58,882
We know you couldn't put
your name in here,

633
00:55:00,291 --> 00:55:02,020
so we all signed our own.

634
00:55:04,428 --> 00:55:05,520
Thank you.

635
00:55:07,832 --> 00:55:11,666
Come on, now. Come on.

636
00:55:49,207 --> 00:55:53,143
Churches over two counties
signed our books. All for you and me.

637
00:55:57,114 --> 00:55:58,479
It's beautiful.

638
00:56:01,786 --> 00:56:02,912
What's wrong?

639
00:56:09,126 --> 00:56:11,594
I got a job offer from Harper and Row
in New York.

640
00:56:12,196 --> 00:56:14,027
Congratulations!

641
00:56:14,165 --> 00:56:17,760
- I'm not taking it.
- What you mean you're not taking it?

642
00:56:17,902 --> 00:56:19,563
I can't just leave you two here

643
00:56:19,704 --> 00:56:22,172
when things are getting bad
from the mess that I created.

644
00:56:22,273 --> 00:56:27,074
No. If bad things happen,
ain't nothing you can do about it.

645
00:56:27,211 --> 00:56:29,611
And now it's for a reason
we can be proud of.

646
00:56:31,849 --> 00:56:33,874
I don't mean to rub salt in your wound,

647
00:56:34,018 --> 00:56:36,578
but you ain't got a good life here
in Jackson.

648
00:56:36,687 --> 00:56:38,120
Plus, your mama's getting better.

649
00:56:38,256 --> 00:56:41,657
You ain't got nothing left here
but enemies in the Junior League.

650
00:56:41,826 --> 00:56:43,760
You done burned every bridge there is.

651
00:56:43,895 --> 00:56:46,386
And you ain't never gonna
get another man in this town.

652
00:56:46,530 --> 00:56:48,760
Everybody know that.

653
00:56:48,900 --> 00:56:52,336
So don't walk your white butt
to New York, run it!

654
00:56:54,305 --> 00:56:58,002
Looky here, Miss Skeeter.
I'm gonna take care of Aibileen.

655
00:57:00,177 --> 00:57:01,974
And she's gonna take care of me.

656
00:57:13,724 --> 00:57:16,215
Go find your life, Miss Skeeter.

657
00:57:29,774 --> 00:57:32,174
Aibileen, can you come in here, please?

658
00:57:38,282 --> 00:57:39,340
Good morning.

659
00:57:40,084 --> 00:57:44,987
Aibileen, the silver
I lent Elizabeth last week.

660
00:57:45,122 --> 00:57:47,249
It not polished good?

661
00:57:47,358 --> 00:57:50,657
Humidity been fighting me
on polishing day.

662
00:57:50,795 --> 00:57:55,494
When you returned it, three pieces
were missing from the felt wrapper.

663
00:57:56,801 --> 00:58:00,066
A fork and two spoons.

664
00:58:00,237 --> 00:58:03,798
Let me... Let me go check in the
kitchen. Maybe I left some behind.

665
00:58:03,941 --> 00:58:07,001
You know as well as I do that silver's
not in the kitchen.

666
00:58:09,313 --> 00:58:11,611
You check in Mae Mobley's bed?

667
00:58:12,683 --> 00:58:14,810
Since the Lil Man was born,
she been putting things...

668
00:58:14,952 --> 00:58:16,715
Do you hear her, Elizabeth?

669
00:58:17,722 --> 00:58:19,553
She's trying to blame it on a toddler.

670
00:58:21,692 --> 00:58:23,387
I ain't got no silver.

671
00:58:23,527 --> 00:58:25,654
She says she doesn't have them.

672
00:58:26,130 --> 00:58:30,396
Then it behooves me to inform you
that you are fired, Aibileen.

673
00:58:31,502 --> 00:58:33,697
And I'll be calling the police.

674
00:58:35,606 --> 00:58:38,404
Aibee, my throat hurts.

675
00:58:40,544 --> 00:58:43,308
I'll go get some syrup, Miss Leefolt.

676
00:58:43,981 --> 00:58:46,506
Elizabeth can take care
of her own children.

677
00:58:49,887 --> 00:58:52,754
- I'll go get the cough syrup.
- Come here, Lil Man.

678
00:58:52,890 --> 00:58:54,357
I'm OK.

679
00:59:04,702 --> 00:59:06,761
I didn't steal no silver.

680
00:59:06,904 --> 00:59:10,670
Maybe I can't send you to jail
for what you wrote,

681
00:59:10,775 --> 00:59:12,709
but I can send you for being a thief.

682
00:59:12,843 --> 00:59:15,277
I know something about you.
Don't you forget that.

683
00:59:15,980 --> 00:59:19,108
From what Yule Mae says, there's a lot
of time to write letters in jail.

684
00:59:19,250 --> 00:59:22,947
Plenty of time to write the truth
about you. And the paper is free.

685
00:59:23,087 --> 00:59:25,783
- Nobody will believe what you wrote!
- I don't know!

686
00:59:26,323 --> 00:59:29,622
I been told I'm a pretty good writer.
Already sold a lot of books.

687
00:59:34,365 --> 00:59:36,629
Call the police, Elizabeth.

688
00:59:37,268 --> 00:59:40,032
All you do is scare and lie
to try to get what you want.

689
00:59:40,137 --> 00:59:41,161
Aibileen, stop!

690
00:59:41,338 --> 00:59:43,397
You a godless woman.

691
00:59:45,409 --> 00:59:47,502
Ain't you tired, Miss Hilly?

692
00:59:50,147 --> 00:59:51,512
Ain't you tired?

693
01:00:04,929 --> 01:00:07,397
Aibileen, you have to go now.

694
01:00:21,979 --> 01:00:24,447
Don't go, Aibee.

695
01:00:25,616 --> 01:00:27,982
Baby, you need to get back to bed.

696
01:00:28,486 --> 01:00:32,547
- Please don't leave.
- I gots to, baby. I am so sorry.

697
01:00:32,723 --> 01:00:35,487
Are you going to take care
of another little girl?

698
01:00:35,626 --> 01:00:37,617
No, that's not the reason.

699
01:00:37,761 --> 01:00:41,322
I don't want to leave you,
but it's time for me to retire.

700
01:00:41,465 --> 01:00:43,763
- You're my last little girl.
- No!

701
01:00:43,868 --> 01:00:45,893
Baby. Baby.

702
01:00:46,871 --> 01:00:49,431
I need you to remember everything
I told you, OK?

703
01:00:49,540 --> 01:00:51,701
- OK.
- You remember what I told you?

704
01:00:51,842 --> 01:00:57,303
You is kind. You is smart.

705
01:00:57,448 --> 01:00:59,143
You is important.

706
01:00:59,283 --> 01:01:01,183
That's right, Baby Girl.

707
01:01:06,357 --> 01:01:07,847
Don't go, Aibee.

708
01:01:07,992 --> 01:01:09,220
I gots to, baby.

709
01:01:11,862 --> 01:01:13,830
You give my sweet girl a chance.

710
01:01:30,114 --> 01:01:32,378
<i>Mae Mobley was my last baby.</i>

711
01:01:34,818 --> 01:01:37,719
<i>In just ten minutes,</i>
<i>the only life I knew was done.</i>

712
01:01:37,855 --> 01:01:40,585
Aibee!

713
01:01:43,928 --> 01:01:46,055
<i>God says we need to love our enemies.</i>

714
01:01:46,197 --> 01:01:47,562
No!

715
01:01:49,466 --> 01:01:50,831
<i>It hard to do.</i>

716
01:01:57,041 --> 01:01:59,202
<i>But it can start by telling the truth.</i>

717
01:02:04,348 --> 01:02:07,943
<i>No one had ever asked me</i>
<i>what it felt like to be me.</i>

718
01:02:11,288 --> 01:02:13,381
<i>Once I told the truth about that...</i>

719
01:02:15,359 --> 01:02:17,054
<i>...I felt free.</i>

720
01:02:25,436 --> 01:02:28,564
<i>And I got to thinking</i>
<i>about all the people I know.</i>

721
01:02:30,574 --> 01:02:32,599
<i>And the things I seen and done.</i>

722
01:02:38,315 --> 01:02:42,684
<i>My boy, Treelore, always said we going</i>
<i>to have a writer in the family one day.</i>

723
01:02:45,990 --> 01:02:48,151
<i>I guess it's gonna be me.</i>
